    {
      "title": "The Problem with Color Pickers",
      "text": [

        "Some tools, like Adobe Kuler, give users complete control over individual colors. They’re highly precise but not always intuitive or fast. That level of detail is useful when refining an existing palette, but my research showed that most designers start from scratch.",
        "Color Supply takes a different approach. Instead of starting with endless options, users explore premade color palettes—selecting and refining them as they go. Start with a base, then customize as needed. The result? A faster, more creative workflow."
      ]
